sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J07024
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: ToxR'::scFv Fusion 1 (with promoter and rbs and terminator)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jenmitch
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The first of three fusions between ToxR', a modified dimerizing protein, and an anti-fluorescein binding scFv sequence. ToxR', active as a dimer, binds to the ctx promoter sequence (BBa_J07007) to initiate transcription. This part is designed to respond to a fluorescein dimer and activate the ctx promoter.

The restriction sites flagged below were introduced to allow for protein fusions, and are not to be removed. See ToxR' (J07009) for details.
